snippet.title: MUST SEE! - Barron Trump Mission Trip To Africa Singing About God
snippet.description:
MUST SEE! - Barron Trump Mission Trip To Africa Singing About God


⬇️⬇️⬇️ Watch more videos below! ⬇️⬇️⬇️
https://youtu.be/WBHJZs8ZeFQ
https://youtu.be/GAdihLnAiXk
https://youtu.be/SZZW8YMZlMg?si=kP7ZE5s5fhhjjpX2
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=hq_JjAodbY0

[Verse 1]
I flew in thinkin’ I had somethin’ to give
But they showed me how the faithful live
Barefoot kids with the brightest eyes
Thankin’ God under open skies

[Chorus]
I saw God in the hands of a child
In a song that rose through the heat and wild
I didn’t come to save — I came to see
What love looks like when it’s wild and free
Africa whispered through the wind and dust:
“Barron, love like Jesus — serve and trust”

[Verse 2]
We built a wall, we shared some bread
They gave me peace with every word they said
No lights, no gold, just hearts on fire
Praising God like a gospel choir

[Chorus – Repeat]
I saw God in the hands of a child
In a song that rose through the heat and wild
I didn’t come to save — I came to see
What love looks like when it’s wild and free
Africa whispered through the wind and dust:
“Barron, love like Jesus — serve and trust”

[Outro – Spoken softly]
"They had nothing... but gave me everything."
"In the dust, I found the light."
